Because of , two waves (the first and second in Eq.())
 have amplitudes of the same magnitude. As we will see alter, the absolute square of the
 amplitude of a wave must somewhat be proportional to the flux of
 particle. Hence we conclude that the wave function of Eq.()
 describes the situation in which an ingoing wave is reflected
 back to an outgoing wave by the potential step. This
 interpretation is in accordance with the classical picture of
 what the particle goes on. The wave function 
 in Eq.() with  describes the
 penetration of the Schrodinger wave into the classically
 forbidden region of . The amplitude of penetrating
 wave decreases exponentially as we go further into the forbidden
 region, and at large distance from the potential barrier the
 amplitude is for all practical purpose zero in accordance with
 the classical picture.

